OL,7,F"I had a job interview, (I) tried to
OL,8,Fcover my tag. (I) get there and he
OL,9,Flooks down at my ankle and screws his
OL,10,Fface. Obviously I didn't get the job."
OL,12,FEven with the obvious hurdles that
OL,13,Ftagging poses for offenders, it still
OL,14,Fremains a pivotal part of the criminal
OL,15,Fjustice system.
OL,17,FIn 2019 the Mayor of London and
OL,18,FMinistry of Justice launched the knife
OL,19,Fcrime tagging pilot scheme.
