OL,7,FUltimately what we have here is a
OL,8,Fphilosophical disagreement about who
OL,9,Fis responsible for tagging offenders.
OL,11,FWhile the MoJ accept that its their
OL,12,Fprobation officers who put tags on
OL,13,Foffenders, they say that they are
OL,14,Fsimply following the guidance set by
OL,15,FMOPAC.
OL,17,FMOPAC accept that while they set the
OL,18,Fguidance under this scheme probation
OL,19,Fofficers have the final say so on who
OL,20,Fgets tagged.
